<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JUN 94 / UK Company News: Hemingway buys
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Hemingway Properties is to acquire the head leasehold interest in Templars
Square shopping centre at Cowley, Oxford, for Pounds 16m.
Templars Square, which was developed in 1965 and refurbished in 1989,
consists of 87 individual units providing a total of about 240,000 sq ft of
retail space. Net initial income is Pounds 1.4m a year, expected to increase
to about Pounds 1.6m a year over the next three years.
