<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JUN 94 / UK Company News: BA chief pay rise
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
In his first full year as chairman of British Airways, Sir Colin Marshall
received a 19 per cent increase in his total pay, from Pounds 663,830 to
Pounds 788,019.
During the 12 months to March 31 BA's pre-tax profits rose 63 per cent to
Pounds 301m, against Pounds 185m.
Sir Colin, the highest paid director, received an increase to Pounds 492,662
(Pounds 429,949) in his basic salary with a further performance related
Pounds 61,750 this time. Of the comparative figure Pounds 86,691 related to
his period from being appointed chairman in February 1993.
</TEXT>
