<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JUN 94 / UK Company News: Umeco in black
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Umeco, the USM-traded aircraft refueller manufacturer and seals and sealants
concern, ended the year to March 31 with pre-tax profits of Pounds 511,000.
Last time saw losses, FRS 3-adjusted, of Pounds 144,000.
Directors said the performance reflected a lower cost base and the
introduction of new products and services.
Turnover rose from Pounds 11m to Pounds 13.4m, including Pounds 1m from
acquisitions. Earnings per share were 3.53p (3.4p losses) and an increased
final dividend of 1.25p lifts the total from 1.75p to 2p.
</TEXT>
