FT  14 JUN 94 / UK Company News: Exceptional gain cuts Prospect loss to
Pounds 0.5m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Prospect Industries, the specialist engineer, reported a lower seasonal loss
of Pounds 489,000 pre-tax for the six months to March 31, against Pounds
1.24m. The result was helped by an exceptional gain of Pounds 736,000
arising from the sale of a loan note.
Mr Philip Wilbraham, chairman, said the company continued to operate in an
aggressive and competitive environment. However, it had won a record number
of orders, including increased work overseas.
He added: 'At this stage of the year the future looks encouraging.'
Taking into account the outlook the interim dividend is raised from 0.275p
to 0.29p. Losses per share were down at 0.08p (0.56p) or 0.05p (0.43p) fully
diluted.
Turnover slipped to Pounds 21.4m against Pounds 22.1m including Pounds
594,000 from discontinued activities. The operating loss from continuing
activities was lower at Pounds 1.01m (Pounds 1.03m).
