companies in October 1992. For a period of about 18 months Cannon sold
mortgage packages, produced by C&amp;G Guardian, a centralised mortgage lender
taken over by C&amp;G in 1990.
Cannon claims no fees have been paid since January 1993. A writ was issued
last week.
