</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Talks between the BBC and its main unions continued at Acas, the
conciliation service, last night amid hopes that a settlement can be reached
to the dispute that has already caused two 24-hour strikes.
Further industrial action planned for today has been called off pending the
outcome of the talks, which will continue today.
