<HEADLINE>
FT  13 JUN 94 / Observer: Going begging
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Nice to see Lady Margaret Colville made Companion of the Royal Victorian
Order in the latest honours list. As 'Extra Woman of the Bedchamber to Queen
Elizabeth the Queen Mother', she no doubt deserves it.
And something for below stairs, too: Royal Victorian Medals (Silver) to  -
among others - Henry Charles Bynoth (roofing contractor), Christopher Arthur
Chiverton (trapper, Great Park, Crown Estate, Windsor) and Peter Horace
Matthews (senior sous chef, Buckingham palace).
Nothing for the corgis?
</TEXT>
