FT  13 JUN 94 / Business Travel: Tunnel fire
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
An explosion on Saturday caused a serious fire in a rail tunnel being built
under the Great Belt waterway between Denmark's main islands at the mouth of
the Baltic.
Storebaelt A/S (Great Belt), the construction group responsible for the
project, said the fire lasted eight hours before being brought under
control.
The tunnel is part of a 20bn crown (Dollars 3bn) road/rail/tunnel/bridge
link between Zealand island and the European mainland, via Funen.
